gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 104, Celtics 91
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Celtics, 104-91. Patrick Beverley recorded a team-high 20 points, along with 10 rebounds and three assists for the Bucks, while Brook Lopez (15 points, six rebounds, five 3PM) and Bobby Portis (15 points, 10 rebounds) added a combined 30 points in the victory. Jaylen Brown tallied 14 points, 10 rebounds, three assists and four steals for the Celtics in the losing effort. The Bucks snap a four-game losing streak as they improve to 48-31 on the season, while the Celtics fall to 62-17.
